Former Governor of Ondo State, Dr. Olusegun Mimiko, leader of the Zenith Labour Party (ZLP), at the weekend slammed incumbent Governor Rotimi Akeredolu as an unprogressive governor.
Mimiko berating Akeredolu who accused him of abandoning several projects left behind by his predecessor, late Governor Olusegun Agagu. Mimiko hosting Deputy Governor Agboola Ajayi of Ondo State, ZLP governorship candidate, at his country home, scolded Governor Akeredolu who he said abandoned the reproductive health care programme in Ondo State.